org.apache.tamaya.spi

Class PropertyValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.tamaya.spi.PropertyValue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class PropertyValue
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Class modelling the result of a request for a property value. A property value is basically identified by its key. There might be reasons, where one want to further analyze, which PropertySources provided a value and which not, so it is possible to create a PropertyValue with a null value. Nevertheless in all cases the provider source (typically the name of the PropertySource) must be set.
    See Also:
